2020-09-16 03:58:10-05:00,New PACTA tool to help banks finance journey to Paris Agreement,"2C Investing Initiative launches new initaitive to support growing band of banks committed to bringing their investments into line with the Paris Agreement An open-source toolkit to help banks analyse their loan books against the Paris Agreement Capital Transition Assessment (PACTA) methodology, and act accordingly to decarbonise their investments, has been made available by non-profit think tank the 2C Investing Initiative. Drawing on a huge climate-related financial database, PACTA for Banks uses forward-looking asset-level information on, for example, the production plans of a car manufacturing plant for the next five years or the climate risk management of a firm at the boardroom level. It then produces a confidential report from which banks can make lending decisions based on their own climate targets. The free tool enables users to measure the alignment of their corporate lending portfolios with climate scenarios across key climate-relevant sectors and technologies, the think tank said.",BCS,en,BusinessGreen
