2020-01-04 00:24:37-05:00,Staff takeover deals in IT see retention perks,"When large global companies hand over their IT operations to Indian IT services companies for modernisation, the latter are often compelled to offer generous transition bonuses — or stay bonuses as some call it — to domain experts that come from the former.Indian IT has seen about a dozen such contracts in the past two years as clients seek their expertise for digital transformation. HCL took over the IT operations of Barclays and Broadcom, TCS of Transamerica, Wipro of Alight, and Infosys of Hitachi and Verizon.In such deals, customers usually identify 25-30 of their employees, who are key to their processes and operations, and who they would like the IT services company to retain. But since those employees are often not eager to transition to the Indian company — in some cases they worry that they will not be retained for long — it becomes imperative to offer them transition bonuses. Sometimes the IT services company itself wants to retain these people for the long term, considering their expertise.The bonuses range between 10% and 20% of the annual compensation, and can go up to even 30% where the domain skills are critical.",BCS,en,The Economic Times India
